# Clean & scalable code

Complements the layering in `recall.mdc` / `recall-api.mdc` and the gate in `execution.mdc`.
Be concrete, not clever. Optimize real bottlenecks — don't gold-plate.

## Structure & placement
- Keep files focused. If one exceeds ~300 lines or mixes concerns, split it (extract hooks,
  components, helpers). Screens stay thin — logic in hooks, not the screen.
- Put code in the right layer: routers thin → services (logic) → gateways/repositories (IO).
  Mobile: all network in `lib/api.ts`, UI in components, state/logic in hooks/contexts.
- No dead code, commented-out blocks, or duplicated logic — extract a shared helper.
- Name by intent; no magic numbers (use named constants / config).

## Performance (snappy & smooth)
- Never block the user path with best-effort work — push it to background jobs; it must never
  raise into the request/stream.
- Kill waterfalls: batch independent calls (`asyncio.gather` / `Promise.all`), don't `await` in a
  loop. Paginate; never fetch-all-then-filter.
- Cache hot/repeated reads (Redis on the backend; React state/memo on mobile) and invalidate on
  write. Don't refetch on every render.
- Backend: no N+1 queries — one query + existing indexes; release the DB connection during the
  model stream.
- Mobile: `React.memo` / `useMemo` + stable callbacks for expensive renders; never do heavy work
  (e.g. full markdown re-parse) per streamed token; keep FlashList items cheap.

## Correctness (not buggy / not sloppy)
- Surface errors — no silent empty `catch`. Validate inputs (Pydantic on the backend).
- Clean up: clear timers/listeners/sockets on unmount; cancel in-flight work when inputs change.
- Add/adjust tests for new logic, and finish green (`./scripts/dev.sh check`).
